Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 14:14:20 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 14/17] feat(india): wire forward-outlook into Fundamental
 Health composite + tier-shift verdict
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

User reported MTAR Tech showing Concall Score 85/A and FORWARD STRONG
but Fundamental Health stuck at 56/B and verdict NEUTRAL — the strong
forward signal wasn't actually moving the headline numbers. Guidance
should play a crucial role.

Three changes:

A. SIXTH FUNDAMENTAL COMPONENT
   When a concall is provided, fundamentalScore.components now includes
   a 'forward' tile alongside growth / margin / WC / promoter /
   cash_conversion. Score derived from concallScore (0-100) with a small
   adjustment from explicit guidance direction:
    - 'raised'    → base + 10
    - 'lowered'   → base − 15
    - 'introduced' / 'maintained' → base unchanged
   Capped 0-100. The Fundamental Components row shows 6 cards instead
   of 5 when present.

B. RE-WEIGHTED COMPOSITE
   With forward present, weights become:
     growth 22% · margin 20% · WC 12% · promoter 10% · cash 11% · forward 25%
   Without forward, original 30/25/15/15/15 weighting unchanged.
   Forward gets the largest single weight because the user reasonably
   asks for it to play a crucial role — a strong concall is the single
   best predictor of next-quarter performance.

   Direction also tilts on forward: forward ≥75 + composite ≥50 →
   'improving' (lifts moderate fundamentals when commentary is bullish);
   forward ≤30 + composite ≤60 → 'deteriorating'.

C. VERDICT TIER SHIFT
   buildTopLineVerdict now post-processes the verdict against forward
   score. Verdict tiers ordered SELL → AVOID → NEUTRAL → HOLD →
   ACCUMULATE → BUY.
    - forward ≥80 (very positive concall): bump verdict up one tier
    - forward ≤25 (weak concall): bump verdict down one tier
   Pinned at extremes (BUY can't go higher, SELL can't go lower).

Effect for MTAR:
   Before: composite 56/B, NEUTRAL · FORWARD: STRONG
   After:  composite ~64/B+, ACCUMULATE · FORWARD: STRONG
   (forward score 85+10 dir-bonus = 95 lifts composite via 25% weight,
   then tier-shifts NEUTRAL → HOLD → ACCUMULATE)

Effect for any India ticker:
 - Concall now has measurable impact on the headline grade and verdict
 - Fundamental Components UI row gets a 'Forward Outlook' tile when a
   transcript is uploaded
 - Without a transcript the report works exactly as before (5-component
   composite, no shift)

